        <prompt>How did the Mexican Revolution affect U.S. border states?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">It had no effect</option>
            <option letter="b">It led to increased immigration and border tensions</option>
            <option letter="c">It improved economic relations</option>
            <option letter="d">It created new states</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>The Mexican Revolution caused increased Mexican immigration to U.S. border states, created security concerns after Pancho Villa's raids, and led to military interventions and border tensions.</explanation>
