    <question>
        <prompt>What was the significance of the Hull House?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">It was a government building</option>
            <option letter="b">It provided social services to immigrants</option>
            <option letter="c">It was a military facility</option>
            <option letter="d">It was a luxury hotel</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>Hull House, founded by Jane Addams, was a settlement house that provided educational, cultural, and social services to immigrants and the poor, becoming a model for social reform efforts.</explanation>
    </question>

    <question>
        <prompt>How did World War I affect women's roles in society?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Women were restricted to domestic roles</option>
            <option letter="b">Women took on new industrial and civic roles</option>
            <option letter="c">Women were banned from working</option>
            <option letter="d">Women's roles remained unchanged</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>WWI led women to take on new roles in industry, civic organizations, and public life as they filled jobs vacated by men serving in the military, contributing to support for women's suffrage.</explanation>
